title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {B}]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\times  p]]></fr:tex> matrix, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {C}]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p\times  q]]></fr:tex> matrix. Then
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[(\mathbf {A}\mathbf {B})\mathbf {C} = \mathbf {A}(\mathbf {B}\mathbf {C}).]]></fr:tex>
In other words, matrix multiplication is associative.</fr:p>
 
   
